		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Shanter&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>You can hunt in the ShadeWeavers thicket area, as well as the Paludal Caverns by the SWT zone lines.<br><br>In PC stick with the low level shrooms, and bugs, stay away from the fiends, they don't really seem to be worth the effort.&nbsp;&nbsp;They hit you with an extremely long lasting DOT, spreading crud, that can really ruin your playing fund.<br><br>I would recommend staying away from Hollowshade Moor unless you are in a decent group.  The beasties there seem to con lower than they should.<br><br>One good note is that the Shar Vahl Bards guild seems to have nearly all of the Norathian bard songs in one location, and the rest are either in Katta or Shadow Haven.<br><br>If hunting in ShadeWeavers Thicket, you would probably hunt the brigands, bigger hoppers and the Shak Dratha or their brown cousins (fergot the names -- looks like the ETs from &quot;Aliens Attack&quot;) Beware, there is a range of mountains splitting SWT with a very narrow pass, and on the other side the beasties con blue, yellow and red to my 32 ranger.<br><br>Happy hunting,<br><br>Shantune, VahShir, Bard 27, Ayonae Roe</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td></tr></table>
